configuration/README.md
     1‚Üí# Configuration
     3‚ÜíThis section details the configuration options available in the ***book.toml***:
     4‚Üí- **[General]** configuration including the `book`, `rust`, `build` sections
     5‚Üí- **[Preprocessor]** configuration for default and custom book preprocessors
     6‚Üí- **[Renderer]** configuration for the HTML, Markdown and custom renderers
     7‚Üí- **[Environment Variable]** configuration for overriding configuration options in your environment
     8‚Üí
     9‚Üí[General]: general.md
    10‚Üí[Preprocessor]: preprocessors.md
    11‚Üí[Renderer]: renderers.md
    12‚Üí[Environment Variable]: environment-variables.md

configuration/environment-variables.md
     1‚Üí# Environment variables
     3‚ÜíAll configuration values can be overridden from the command line by setting the
     4‚Üícorresponding environment variable. Because many operating systems restrict
     5‚Üíenvironment variables to be alphanumeric characters or `_`, the configuration
     6‚Üíkey needs to be formatted slightly differently to the normal `foo.bar.baz` form.
     7‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶

