    71‚Üí### Optional backends
    84‚Üí## HTML renderer options
    86‚ÜíThe HTML renderer has a variety of options detailed below.
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   176‚Üí### `[output.html.print]`
   191‚Üí### `[output.html.fold]`
   206‚Üí### `[output.html.playground]`
   230‚Üí### `[output.html.code]`
   244‚Üí### `[output.html.search]`
   286‚Üí#### `[output.html.search.chapter]`
   288‚ÜíThe [`output.html.search.chapter`] table provides the ability to modify search settings per chapter or directory. Each key is the path to the chapter source file or directory, and the value is a table of settings to apply to that path. This will merge recursively, with more specific paths taking precedence.
   289‚Üí
   290‚Üí```toml
   291‚Üí[output.html.search.chapter]
   292‚Üí# Disables search indexing for all chapters in the `appendix` directory.
   293‚Üí"appendix" = { enable = false }
   294‚Üí# Enables search indexing for just this one appendix chapter.
   295‚Üí"appendix/glossary.md" = { enable = true }
   296‚Üí```
   297‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   300‚Üí### `[output.html.redirect]`
   325‚Üí## Markdown renderer
   327‚ÜíThe Markdown renderer will run preprocessors and then output the resulting
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶

