mathjax.md
     1‚Üí# MathJax support
     3‚ÜímdBook has optional support for math equations through
     4‚Üí[MathJax](https://www.mathjax.org/).
     5‚Üí
     6‚ÜíTo enable MathJax, you need to add the `mathjax-support` key to your `book.toml`
     7‚Üíunder the `output.html` section.
     8‚Üí
     9‚Üí```toml
    10‚Üí[output.html]
    11‚Üímathjax-support = true
    12‚Üí```
    13‚Üí
    14‚Üí>**Note:** The usual delimiters MathJax uses are not yet supported. You can't
    15‚Üícurrently use `$$ ... $$` as delimiters and the `\[ ... \]` delimiters need an
    16‚Üíextra backslash to work. Hopefully this limitation will be lifted soon.
    17‚Üí
    18‚Üí>**Note:** When you use double backslashes in MathJax blocks (for example in
    19‚Üí> commands such as `\begin{cases} \frac 1 2 \\ \frac 3 4 \end{cases}`) you need
    20‚Üí> to add _two extra_ backslashes (e.g., `\begin{cases} \frac 1 2 \\\\ \frac 3 4
    21‚Üí> \end{cases}`).
    22‚Üí
    23‚Üí
    24‚Üí### Inline equations
    32‚Üí### Block equations

