summary.md
     1‚Üí# SUMMARY.md
     3‚ÜíThe summary file is used by mdBook to know what chapters to include, in what
     4‚Üíorder they should appear, what their hierarchy is and where the source files
     5‚Üíare. Without this file, there is no book.
     6‚Üí
     7‚ÜíThis markdown file must be named `SUMMARY.md`. Its formatting
     8‚Üíis very strict and must follow the structure outlined below to allow for easy
     9‚Üíparsing. Any element not specified below, be it formatting or textual, is likely
    10‚Üíto be ignored at best, or may cause an error when attempting to build the book.
    11‚Üí
    12‚Üí### Structure
    93‚Üí### Example

theme/README.md
     1‚Üí# Theme
     3‚ÜíThe default renderer uses a [handlebars](https://handlebarsjs.com) template to
     4‚Üírender your markdown files and comes with a default theme included in the mdBook
     5‚Üíbinary.
     6‚Üí
     7‚ÜíThe theme is totally customizable, you can selectively replace every file from
     8‚Üíthe theme by your own by adding a `theme` directory next to `src` folder in your
     9‚Üíproject root. Create a new file with the name of the file you want to override
    10‚Üíand now that file will be used instead of the default file.
    11‚Üí
    12‚ÜíHere are the files you can override:
    13‚Üí
    14‚Üí- **_index.hbs_** is the handlebars template.
    15‚Üí- **_head.hbs_** is appended to the HTML `<head>` section.
    16‚Üí- **_header.hbs_** content is appended on top of every book page.
    17‚Üí- **_css/_** contains the CSS files for styling the book.
    18‚Üí    - **_css/chrome.css_** is for UI elements.
    19‚Üí    - **_css/general.css_** is the base styles.
    20‚Üí    - **_css/print.css_** is the style for printer output.
    21‚Üí    - **_css/variables.css_** contains variables used in other CSS files.
    22‚Üí- **_book.js_** is mostly used to add client side functionality, like hiding /
    23‚Üí  un-hiding the sidebar, changing the theme, ...
    24‚Üí- **_highlight.js_** is the JavaScript that is used to highlight code snippets,
    25‚Üí  you should not need to modify this.
    26‚Üí- **_highlight.css_** is the theme used for the code highlighting.
    27‚Üí- **_favicon.svg_** and **_favicon.png_** the favicon that will be used. The SVG
    28‚Üí  version is used by [newer browsers].
    29‚Üí- **fonts/fonts.css** contains the definition of which fonts to load.
    30‚Üí  Custom fonts can be included in the `fonts` directory.
    31‚Üí
    32‚ÜíGenerally, when you want to tweak the theme, you don't need to override all the
    33‚Üífiles. If you only need changes in the stylesheet, there is no point in
    34‚Üíoverriding all the other files. Because custom files take precedence over
    35‚Üíbuilt-in ones, they will not get updated with new fixes / features.
    36‚Üí
    37‚Üí**Note:** When you override a file, it is possible that you break some
    38‚Üífunctionality. Therefore I recommend to use the file from the default theme as
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶

theme/editor.md
     1‚Üí# Editor
     3‚ÜíIn addition to providing runnable code playgrounds, mdBook optionally allows them
     4‚Üíto be editable. In order to enable editable code blocks, the following needs to
     5‚Üíbe added to the ***book.toml***:
     6‚Üí
     7‚Üí```toml
     8‚Üí[output.html.playground]
     9‚Üíeditable = true
    10‚Üí```
    11‚Üí
    12‚ÜíAfter enabling editable code blocks, the `editable` attribute must be added to a
    13‚Üícode block to make it editable:
    14‚Üí
    15‚Üí~~~markdown
    16‚Üí```rust,editable
    17‚Üífn main() {
    18‚Üí    let number = 5;
    19‚Üí    print!("{}", number);
    20‚Üí}
    21‚Üí```
    22‚Üí~~~
    23‚Üí
    24‚ÜíThe above will result in this editable playground:
    25‚Üí
    26‚Üí```rust,editable
    27‚Üífn main() {
    28‚Üí    let number = 5;
    29‚Üí    print!("{}", number);
    30‚Üí}
    31‚Üí```
    32‚Üí
    33‚ÜíNote the new `Undo Changes` button in the editable playgrounds.
    34‚Üí
    35‚Üí## Customizing the editor
    37‚ÜíBy default, the editor is the [Ace](https://ace.c9.io/) editor, but, if desired,
    38‚Üíthe functionality may be overridden by providing a different folder:
    39‚Üí
    40‚Üí```toml
    41‚Üí[output.html.playground]
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶

theme/index-hbs.md
     1‚Üí# index.hbs
     3‚Üí`index.hbs` is the handlebars template that is used to render the book. The
     4‚Üímarkdown files are processed to html and then injected in that template.
     5‚Üí
     6‚ÜíIf you want to change the layout or style of your book, chances are that you
     7‚Üíwill have to modify this template a little bit. Here is what you need to know.
     8‚Üí
     9‚Üí## Data
    11‚ÜíA lot of data is exposed to the handlebars template with the "context". In the
    12‚Üíhandlebars template you can access this information by using
    13‚Üí
    14‚Üí```handlebars
    15‚Üí{{name_of_property}}
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
    41‚Üí## Handlebars helpers
    43‚ÜíIn addition to the properties you can access, there are some handlebars helpers
    44‚Üíat your disposal.
    45‚Üí
    46‚Üí### toc
    48‚ÜíThe toc helper is used like this
    49‚Üí
    50‚Üí```handlebars
    51‚Üí{{#toc}}{{/toc}}
    52‚Üí```
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
