theme/syntax-highlighting.md
     1‚Üí# Syntax highlighting
     3‚ÜímdBook uses [Highlight.js](https://highlightjs.org) with a custom theme
     4‚Üífor syntax highlighting.
     5‚Üí
     6‚ÜíAutomatic language detection has been turned off, so you will probably want to
     7‚Üíspecify the programming language you use like this:
     8‚Üí
     9‚Üí~~~markdown
    10‚Üí```rust
    11‚Üífn main() {
    12‚Üí    // Some code
    13‚Üí}
    14‚Üí```
    15‚Üí~~~
    16‚Üí
    17‚Üí## Supported languages
    19‚ÜíThese languages are supported by default, but you can add more by supplying
    20‚Üíyour own `highlight.js` file:
    21‚Üí
    22‚Üí- apache
    23‚Üí- armasm
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
    68‚Üí## Custom theme
    69‚ÜíLike the rest of the theme, the files used for syntax highlighting can be
    70‚Üíoverridden with your own.
    71‚Üí
    72‚Üí- ***highlight.js*** normally you shouldn't have to overwrite this file, unless
    73‚Üí  you want to use a more recent version.
      ‚Üí  ‚Ä¶
    82‚Üí## Improve default theme
    84‚ÜíIf you think the default theme doesn't look quite right for a specific language,
    85‚Üíor could be improved, feel free to [submit a new
    86‚Üíissue](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/issues) explaining what you
    87‚Üíhave in mind and I will take a look at it.
    88‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
